# ============================================================================
# _vmr — zsh completion for gvcgo/version-manager, "🔥 A general version
#         manager for thousands of SDKs with TUI inspired by lazygit" —
#         Go=156 leader bump continuing Axis 101 Lua/Luau bindings via the
#         canonical Go Lua interpreter github.com/yuin/gopher-lua.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/gvcgo/version-manager
#   Maintainer : gvcgo / moqsien
#   License    : MIT
#   Stars      : 1,330
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/gvcgo/version-manager
#   Binary     : vmr  (built from cmd/vmr/main.go, with the
#                root cobra command `Use: "vmr"`)
#   Last push  : 2025-11-20
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   vmr is a polyglot SDK version manager — pick any of the
#   thousands of SDKs in its registry (Go, Node, Python,
#   Java, Ruby, Rust, Deno, Bun, Zig, Crystal, Erlang, Elixir,
#   Haskell, OCaml, PHP, Perl, Lua, Julia, R, Swift, .NET,
#   Kotlin, Scala, Clojure, ... plus every cloud tool from
#   kubectl/helm/terraform/aws-cli/gcloud/azure-cli through
#   buf/bazel/pulumi/ansible to obscure CTF tooling) and vmr
#   downloads, installs, switches between, and uninstalls
#   versions for it.  The TUI is inspired by lazygit.  Plugin
#   surface is Lua-based (gopher-lua interpreter embedded in
#   the binary), so adding support for a new SDK is just a
#   `.lua` file in the plugin index that vmr fetches via
#   `update-plugins`.
#
#   Three execution modes:
#     • global — installed SDK becomes the default in the
#       user shell (~/.vmr/sdks/<sdk>/<version> linked into
#       PATH via shell hook)
#     • session — `eval "$(vmr session-mode)"` opens a sub-
#       shell with the chosen version pinned, leaving the
#       parent shell untouched (nestable when `nested-sessions`
#       is toggled on)
#     • project — `.vmr.lock` in a project root pins SDKs
#       per-directory; vmr auto-switches on `cd`
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/vmr/cli/cli.go +
#                       cmd/vmr/cli/{proxy,install_self,
#                       uninstall_self,use,download_threads,
#                       customed_mirrors}.go + cmd/vmr/cli/
#                       vcli/{show,search,local,uninstall,
#                       completions,sessions,plugin}.go
#                       cobra `&cobra.Command{...}` literals;
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/gvcgo/
#                       version-manager/contents/cmd/vmr/...`)
#
#   vmr [SUBCOMMAND] [args...]
#
#   Subcommands  (Use → Aliases):
#     version (v)                    Show version info of
#                                    version-manager
#     show (S)                       Show available SDKs
#     search (s) <SDK>               Search available versions
#                                    for an SDK
#     use (u, h) <SDK[@VERSION]>     Install and switch to a
#                                    version for an SDK
#     local (l) <SDK>                Show installed versions
#                                    for an SDK
#     installed-sdks (in)            Show installed SDKs
#     installed-info (ii)            Show installed SDK info
#     uninstall (uni, r) <SDK[@VERSION]>
#                                    Uninstall versions for an
#                                    SDK
#     update-plugins (up)            Update plugins for vmr
#                                    (re-fetch the Lua plugin
#                                    index, refresh per-SDK
#                                    handlers)
#     install-self (i, is)           Install version-manager
#                                    onto the current host
#     uninstall-self (Uins)          Uninstall version-manager
#                                    (script-only)
#     set-proxy (sp)                 Set proxy for vmr
#     set-reverse-proxy (sr, srp)    Set reverse proxy for vmr
#     set-download-threads (sdt, st)
#                                    Set default threads number
#                                    for downloading
#     toggle-customed-mirrors (tcm, tm)
#                                    Toggle customized mirrors
#                                    on / off
#     add-completions (ac)           Add auto-completions for
#                                    vmr to current shell
#                                    profile
#     nested-sessions (ns)           Toggle nested sessions
#     is-session-mode (ism)          Show if the current shell
#                                    is in session mode
#
#   Standard cobra auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/yuin/gopher-lua v1.1.1`
#   declared in go.mod — `yuin/gopher-lua` is THE canonical Go
#   Lua VM, maintained by Yuusuke "yuin" Inami
#   (yuin/gopher-lua, 6,100+ stars; the predominant pure-Go
#   Lua 5.1 reimplementation that nearly every Go project
#   embedding Lua reaches for — Tengo? no, that's a different
#   lang; gopher-lua is what Atlassian gostatsd, chartmuseum,
#   chihaya, chproxy, mev-boost-relay, dapr/components-contrib,
#   storj/ipfs-go-ds-storj, openmock, chanify, frangipanni,
#   honeytrap, encoredev/encore-internal, OffchainLabs/nitro,
#   helm/chartmuseum, layotto, helm chartmuseum, gostatsd,
#   and dozens of other production Go applications use to
#   embed Lua scripting).  gopher-lua exposes the typed
#   `lua.NewState() *LState` factory with the
#   `lua.NewState(lua.Options{ CallStackSize, RegistrySize,
#   RegistryMaxSize, RegistryGrowStep, IncludeGoStackTrace,
#   MinimizeStackMemory })` configurable variant, the typed
#   `L.PCall(nargs, nret, errFn)` /
#   `L.CallByParam(P{Fn, NRet, Protect, Handler}, args...)`
#   `L.LoadString(source)` / `L.LoadFile(path)` /
#   `L.DoString(source)` / `L.DoFile(path)` /
#   `L.GetGlobal(name)` / `L.SetGlobal(name, value)` /
#   `L.GetTop()` / `L.SetTop(n)` /
#   `L.Push(value)` / `L.Pop(n)` /
#   `L.CheckString(n)` / `L.CheckInt(n)` /
#   `L.CheckTable(n)` / `L.CheckFunction(n)` /
#   `L.OptString(n, dflt)` / `L.OptInt(n, dflt)` and the
#   full `*LTable` / `*LFunction` / `*LUserData` /
#   `*LChannel` / `LString` / `LNumber` / `LBool` /
#   `LNilType` value-type primitives, the typed `LGFunction`
#   `func(*LState) int` exported-fn signature, the
#   `*LTable.RawSetH(k, v)` / `RawGetH(k)` /
#   `RawSetInt(i, v)` / `RawGetInt(i)` /
#   `RawSetString(s, v)` / `Insert(i, v)` / `Remove(i)` /
#   `Len()` / `ForEach(fn)` table API, the `L.SetMetatable`
#   metatable installer for Go-typed userdata, coroutine
#   integration (`L.NewThread`, `L.Resume`, `L.Status`),
#   and the typed `*lua.ApiError` error variants for diagnostics.
#   vmr's `internal/plugin/...` wraps `lua.NewState()` per
#   SDK plugin invocation, exposes a typed Go-callable surface
#   (`vmr.download(url, sha256, dest)`, `vmr.extract(archive,
#   dest)`, `vmr.symlink(src, dst)`, `vmr.exec(cmd, args)`,
#   `vmr.platform()`, `vmr.arch()`, `vmr.version_re(pattern)`,
#   `vmr.cache(key, value)`, `vmr.fetch(url, opts)`) to the
#   plugin's `.lua` source, then invokes the plugin's
#   `install(version, dest)`, `available_versions(filter)`,
#   `update_versions()` Lua callbacks through `L.CallByParam`.
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/gvcgo/version-manager/contents/go.mod
#       → module github.com/gvcgo/version-manager
#       → github.com/yuin/gopher-lua v1.1.1
#       → github.com/spf13/cobra v1.8.0
#     gh api repos/gvcgo/version-manager/contents/cmd/vmr/
#         main.go
#       → cmd := cli.New(GitTag, GitHash); cmd.Run()
#     gh api repos/gvcgo/version-manager/contents/cmd/vmr/
#         cli/cli.go
#       → rootCmd = &cobra.Command{ Use: "vmr",
#                                     Short: "version manager" }
#       → AddCommand chain registers version, set-proxy,
#                                       set-reverse-proxy, use,
#                                       install-self,
#                                       uninstall-self,
#                                       set-download-threads,
#                                       toggle-customed-mirrors,
#                                       show, search, local,
#                                       installed-sdks,
#                                       installed-info,
#                                       uninstall, add-
#                                       completions, nested-
#                                       sessions, is-session-
#                                       mode, update-plugins
#   This entry is the Go=156 leader bump that continues Axis
#   101 (Lua/Luau bindings) at 2/0/0 following R993 _lune
#   (Rust=156 OPENED the axis on mlua v0.11.6 with luau
